I use SuSE Linux 8.1 and Eclipse 2.1 GTK

By any chance were you setting the max Java heap size from the command line?  It
is recommended that you start with a large heap, like this:

eclipse -vmargs -Xmx256M

This could be a dup of bug 3128.  If we get OutOfMemoryErrors on shutdown, there
is a possibility we will fail to restart.

No more information from originator.
If this is indeed a duplicate, bug 3128 has been fixed and will be available in 
the next integration build.
Please re-open if this is still a problem with the latest integration builds.
Closing.
